        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1967-05-24T07:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1967-05-24T07:45:00-05:00" n="52"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d52">
                <head>52. Memorandum From the President’s Special Assistant (<persName
                        corresp="#p_RWW1" type="from">Rostow</persName>) to President <persName
                        corresp="#p_JLB1" type="to">Johnson</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d52fn1">Source: <persName corresp="#p_JLB1"
                            >Johnson</persName> Library, National Security File, Country File,
                        Middle East Crisis, Vol. I. Top Secret; [<hi rend="italic">codeword not
                            declassified</hi>]. A handwritten “<gloss target="#t_L1">L</gloss>” on
                        the memorandum indicates the President saw it.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1967-05-24T08:45:00-04:00">May 24, 1967, 8:45 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Mr. President:</p>
                <p>[<hi rend="italic">4 paragraphs (8 lines of source text) not
                    declassified</hi>]</p>
                <p>As Tommy Thompson points out in the third attachment,<note n="2" xml:id="d52fn2"
                        >Not printed.</note> “the key question is which of the two aspects of the
                    Soviet public statement they are emphasizing in private.” If private counsel
                    from Moscow remains moderate, there is scope for diplomacy here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RWW1">Walt</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
